  "title": "Marketing Assistant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong>:<br />1. Design Adaptation & Editing – Assist in modifying and adjusting existing design materials, including menus and promotional materials.<br /><br />2. Print & Production Coordination – Work closely with printing vendors to ensure high-quality production and timely delivery of printed materials.<br /><br />3. Marketing Material Preparation – Support the team in preparing design files for print and digital use, ensuring accuracy and consistency.<br /><br />4. Video Shooting & Editing – Assist in capturing and editing short videos for marketing purposes, including social media content and promotional clipsusing TikTok, Jianying , After Effects.<br /><br />5. Canva Design Support – Utilize Canva for quick edits, template-based designs, and social media content creation.<br /><br />6. File & Asset Management – Organize and maintain marketing assets, design templates, and production files for easy access and future use.<br /><br />7. Other marketing and design-related tasks as assigned by the supervisor.<br /><br /><strong>Requirements:</strong><br />1. 1 years of experience in marketing support or graphic designing<br /><br />2. Have basic knowledge in Adobe Photoshop, Illustrator, Canva, and basic video editing software (TikTok, Jianying , After Effects).<br /><br />3. Strong attention to detail, especially in preparing and adjusting design files for print and digital use.<br /><br />4. Ability to manage print production processes, including liaising with vendors and ensuring timely material delivery.<br /><br />5. Basic video shooting and editing skills to create simple marketing content <br /><br />6. Highly organized, proactive, and able to handle multiple tasks efficiently.<br /><br />(Bonus) Experience in working with F&B marketing materials and printproduction.</p>",
